40. Pierio recreatis antro] Suetonius, in his life of Augustus (84, 85), relates that he followed literary pur-suits with great zeal, and dabbled in poetry. He could not have had much time for such pursuits when this ode was written, but he may have said enough to let it be seen that he desired leisure to follow them.
